Paula Schmitz
August 20 at 11:59 AM ·

MUMS WILL BE HERE this SATURDAY August 29th. They will be in Schmitz Electric’s shed. I will be there from noon-4 on Saturday Otherwise call or text. and I can meet you down there. 4384115.
Sponsored by the elementary PTO, the Southland Elementary Robotics team will be selling mums again this fall. We had such good support from the community last year that we were able to buy toolboxes, another team sign and treats for the kids at state. This year we are hoping to build a stand for our playing field and get more parts as they wear out. I’ve had people ask when the sale will be and right now I’m planning it will start on Labor Day weekend. Details later. Thanks again for your continued support of a great program offered at Southland.

shared_text:
Southland Music
June 18 at 11:04 AM ·

Calling all students, alumni, and community members to participate in a virtual choir for Southland Graduation 2020. The seniors have chosen 2 songs for graduation and we would like to make this tradition happen for them. The plan is to have the 2 songs played at graduation on July 17th. If you are interested in participating please email Mrs. Steinkamp jsteinkamp@isd500.k12.mn.us. message Southland Music or Mrs
Steinkamp on Facebook. Recordings have been made and a link will be sent to you if you are willing to participate. Message with what voice part or parts you are able to sing (soprano, alto, tenor, or bass). If you aren't sure what voice part you are that is okay, you can message Mrs. Steinkamp and she will help determine which voice part would be best. Directions on how to submit recordings will be sent with the practice tracks. If you have any questions please don't hesitate to ask. Hope we can all join together in song to support our graduating seniors!

Southland Students First
May 18 at 12:25 PM ·

It is with great regret that Southland Community Education has decided to cancel all in person Community Education activities indefinitely due to safety concerns surrounding the Covid-19 pandemic. This includes Summer Rec and the Pool Bus. Drivers Training is being moved back to start August 17th and we are currently looking for ways to offer our Speed and Agility camp through a virtual medium, more information will be coming as we develop a more concrete plan.

The safety of our kids is our number one priority at this time. If we get to a point where it is determined to be safe to resume large gatherings, we will look into opening some camps and activities back up.

Sam Klaehn
Dean of Students
Southland School District
(507) 582-3568

shared_text:
Southland Schools
November 5, 2019 at 1:22 PM ·

The Southland Elementary and Middle School Student Councils recently partnered with the Adams Lions Club to participate in the Soles4Souls program for the fourth time. Soles4Souls is wearing out poverty by providing short-term relief and long-term solutions. Since Soles4Souls began in 2006, over 30 million pairs of shoes have been distributed in 127 countries and all 50 US states. Together the middle school and elementary students brought in 549 pairs of shoes! Every single one of those pairs makes a difference in peoples’ lives. Thank you to everybody who donated and helped make a difference!

Southland Schools
November 5, 2019 at 1:22 PM ·

The Southland Elementary and Middle School Student Councils recently partnered with the Adams Lions Club to participate in the Soles4Souls program for the fourth time. Soles4Souls is wearing out poverty by providing short-term relief and long-term solutions. Since Soles4Souls began in 2006, over 30 million pairs of shoes have been distributed in 127 countries and all 50 US states. Together the middle school and elementary students brought in 549 pairs of shoes! Every single one of those pairs makes a difference in peoples’ lives. Thank you to everybody who donated and helped make a difference!

The Salvation Army will start accepting Thanksgiving Basket Applications Monday, November 11th until Thursday, November 14th.
Deadline for Thanksgiving Baskets will be Thursday, November 14th at 4:00 pm. (must be checked in by 3:30 pm)

Application hours are:
Monday through Thursday
9-11:30 am and 1-3:30 pm

IF YOU WORK AND CANNOT MAKE IT DURING THIS TIME, CALL 4337-44566 TO MAKE AN APPOINTMENT. Appointments must be set before 9 am Thursday, November 14th.

NO APPLICATIONS WILL BE TAKEN AFTER THE DEADLINE DATE!!!

When applying for the Thanksgiving Applications.
You will need to bring your: Picture ID, Proof of Address, Last 30 days income AND benefit information. If you have any new members(s) to be added to your household; you will need to bring verification of the household member(s) such as; social security card of birth certificate.

If you have not received any services from The Salvation Army since 2015, please check with receptionist or call 507-437-4566 to find out what you need to bring.
